(9327, 'Area Of Interest', 'nabinchaudhary01@gmail.com', '8018177617', 'RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure', 'RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure', '', 'Target role: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Headline: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Location: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Portfolio: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.matpr.2023.06.115', ARRAY['Excel', 'Leadership', 'Auto CAD', 'ETABS', 'SAFE', 'Staad Pro']::text[], ARRAY['Auto CAD', 'ETABS', 'SAFE', 'Staad Pro', 'Excel']::text[], ARRAY['Excel', 'Leadership']::text[], ARRAY['Auto CAD', 'ETABS', 'SAFE', 'Staad Pro', 'Excel']::text[], '', 'Name: Area of Interest | Email: nabinchaudhary01@gmail.com | Phone: 8018177617 | Location: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure', '', 'Target role: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Headline: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Location: RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure | Portfolio: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.matpr.2023.06.115', 'ME | Civil | Passout 2023 | Score 71.2', '71.2', '[{"degree":"ME","branch":"Civil","graduationYear":"2023","score":"71.2","raw":"Other | Year Degree/Education Institution/Board CGPA/Percentage || Other | 2023 M-Tech in Structural Engineering Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee | Roorkee | India 7.895 | 2023 || Other | 2021 B-Tech in Civil Engineering Kalinga Institute of Industrial Technology | Bhubaneswar | India 9.790 | 2021 || Class 12 | 2016 Intermediate (Class XII) National Infotech H. S. School | Birgunj | Nepal 71.20 % | 2016 || Class 10 | 2014 Matriculate (Class X) Shree Siddhi Vinayak School | Kalaiya | Nepal 82.50 % | 2014"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"RCC, Tall Building, Bridge Engineering, Steel Structure","company":"Imported from resume CSV","description":"Proof Checking of Tall Buildings in ETABS and SAFE | Project Assistant (Consultancy Project) | IIT Roorkee | 2022-Present | − I conduct proof checks of Tall and Small Buildings, meticulously evaluating ETABS and SAFE models from consultants. My responsibilities encompassed design validity, precise load application, stiffness modifier accuracy, response spectrum methodology, earthquake load consideration, and wind load calculations using the gust factor method. I further specialized through a dedicated Tall Building course and gained substantial expertise in IS codes. In summary, I possess a proficient grasp of ETABS and SAFE for comprehensive modelling, analysis, and design of buildings superstructures and foundations. Proof Checking of GFC drawings − I conduct proof checks of drawings received from consultants. My role involves reviewing drawings, specifically focusing on Typical General for Construction (GFC) drawings for various structural components of the proposed buildings. I verify whether these GFC drawings adhere to the guidelines outlined in IS 13920 and SP 34. Analysis and Design of Retaining wall − I''ve analysed both cantilever and counterfort retaining walls, verifying stability against overturning, sliding, and soil bearing pressures. I also designed and calculated essential reinforcement for the elements of wall, ensuring structural integrity, and executed precise reinforcement detailing. Non-Destructive Evaluation of Structure − I have conducted non-destructive evaluations of in-progress school buildings, employing Rebound Hammer and Ultrasonic Pulse Velocity tests on key structural elements like beams and columns. Utilizing IS code guidelines (IS 516 - Part 5 - Sec 1 - 2018), I established concrete quality benchmarks for Ultrasonic Pulse Velocity testing. For Rebound Hammer tests, I referenced industry literature for benchmark values. Subsequently, I interpreted the results to assign concrete quality grading. Design of Drain Section − I have designed drain section. I have checked safety of the drain in critical situations and also, I have calculated reinforcement requirements in the element of the drain section. || Pavement composition layers, Design of flexible pavement using IIT Pave software as per IRC 37: 2018, Geometric design of highway and | Transportation Infrastructure: Planning and Design | KIIT Deemed University | 2020-2020 | structural evaluation of flexible pavement. || Surveying and implementation of different road and bridge projects. | Road and Bridge Project | Sagar Nirman Sewa | 2019-2019"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported project details","description":"Lime as an Alternate Binder for Sustainability | Limes are environmental friendly and sustainable. Due to lack of research on traditional knowledge systems and scientific understanding of historic lime mortars, many conservation professionals face severe challenges in implementing the lime works. In this project, Kankar lime (Impure form of lime) was kept at different temperatures for different duration to find out the calcination temperature and duration. Kankar lime was then characterized by using different characterization tools like XRD, XRF, SEM, TGA/DTA. Nabin Chaudhary M-Tech Structural Engineering Contact No: +91 8018177617 Email: nabinchaudhary01@gmail.com, nabin_c@ce.iitr.ac.in | 2022-2023 || Performance of Lightweight Concrete Using Agro-industrial Wastes | Compare the performances of different agro-industrial wastes like oil palm shell, coconut shell, expanded polystyrene, silica fume used as construction material to produce lightweight concrete. 30% replacement of coarse aggregate by these wastes can reduce the weight of the concrete by around 20 - 30%. | 2020-2020"}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported accomplishment","description":"Got Study in Inda Scholarship (full) for M-Tech; Got Compex Scholarship (Indian embassy) for B-Tech; Positions of Responsibility & Extra Curriculars; Officer DC and Logistics | ASCE Student Chapter KIIT University January 2020 - January 2021; The American Society of Civil Engineers represents the civil engineering profession in 177 countries. Founded in 1852, ASCE is the nation’s; oldest engineering society. A platform for student''s professional development, craft leadership, build patience and teamwork. It has helped; me in professional development. Being a part of it I have organized time to time site visit to insight students better exposure to the outside; environment, quizzes, events etc.; Research Publications; Nabin Chaudhary, Ipsita Mohanty, Purnachandra Saha, Riya Kumari, Ashok Kumar Pandey, “Performance of resource saving agro-industrial; wastes and their utilization in lightweight concrete- A review”, in Materials Today: Proceedings, Elsevier, 2023.; https://doi.org/10.1016/j.matpr.2023.06.115; Kundan Samal, Alakh Raj Mohan, Nabin Chaudhary, Sanjib Moulick, \"Application of vermitechnology in waste management: A review on; mechanism and performance\", in Journal of Environmental Chemical Engineering, Elsevier, 2019.; https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jece.2019.103392; References; Dr. Bhupinder Singh; Professor; IIT Roorkee; Bhupinder.singh@ce.iitr.ac.in; +91 8475031000"}]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Nabin Chaudhary.pdf', 'Name: Area Of Interest

